FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1776668725
OL,3,C'Part of the family': much-loved Bury
OL,4,Cshop manager says goodbye after 41
OL,5,Cyears
OL,7,FAnn first opened the Princess Parade
OL,8,Fshop in September 1985, a year later
OL,9,Fthe success of the store was marked in
OL,10,Fa newspaper clipping from The
OL,11,FMessenger, dated March 7th, 1986.
OL,13,FThe article celebrated the shop's
OL,14,Fearly days, highlighting Ann as
OL,15,FManageress and featuring a search for
OL,16,Fthe best Simnel cake, a light fruit
OL,17,Fcake ` a tradition close to the
OL,18,Fbakery's roots.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1776668725
OL,3,C'Part of the family': much-loved Bury
OL,4,Cshop manager says goodbye after 41
OL,5,Cyears
OL,7,FToday, both Ann and the much-loved
OL,8,FSimnel cake remain a proud part of the
OL,9,FGreenhalgh's story.
OL,11,FFounded in 1957, Greenhalgh's Craft
OL,12,FBakery has long been known for its
OL,13,Fstrong community ties, with dedicated
OL,14,Fstaff playing a central role in its
OL,15,Fsuccess.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1776668725
OL,3,C'Part of the family': much-loved Bury
OL,4,Cshop manager says goodbye after 41
OL,5,Cyears
OL,7,F"I love everything about working
OL,8,Fhere," said Ann. "I'm incredibly
OL,9,Fpassionate about what I do ` I
OL,10,Fwouldn't swap it. I've never wanted to
OL,11,Fgo anywhere else. I'm part of the
OL,12,Ffamily here. If you chopped me in
OL,13,Fhalf, I'd be Greenhalgh's through and
OL,14,Fthrough."
OL,16,FAnn recalls the excitement of the
OL,17,Fshop's opening day, with queues
OL,18,Fstretching out the door and counters
OL,19,Ffilled to the brim.
OL,26,@oD@AOUpD@FO]pD@ROUvD@IO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/9
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1776668725
OL,3,C'Part of the family': much-loved Bury
OL,4,Cshop manager says goodbye after 41
OL,5,Cyears
OL,7,F"It was enormous ` such a wonderful
OL,8,Fday." she said.
OL,10,FWhile retail has evolved over the
OL,11,Fyears, Ann believes the heart of the
OL,12,Fshop has remained the same.
OL,14,F"Times have changed, but not the shop.
OL,15,FWe still have that same sense of
OL,16,Fcommunity. I've loved working with
OL,17,Fevery member of the team ` so many
OL,18,Fhave trained here, and some never want
OL,19,Fto leave."
OL,26,@oD@AOUpD@EO]vD@AOU{D@JO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/9
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
